# Dependencies — latest stable

**Version tables & full dependency list:** `techstack.md` § Dependencies

**Goal:** Every dependency on the **latest stable release** within its supported major line. Skill: `upgrade-deps`.

## Stack targets (keep current)

| Package | Policy |
|---------|--------|
| `next` | Latest **16.x** — match `eslint-config-next` major |
| `react` / `react-dom` | Latest **19.x** paired with Next |
| `sanity`, `@sanity/*`, `next-sanity` | Latest **v6 / v7 / v13** line — never downgrade to v5 |
| `tailwindcss`, `@tailwindcss/postcss` | Latest **4.x** |
| `typescript` | Latest **6.x** |
| `zod` | Latest **4.x** — API validation |
| `resend` | Latest — contact email |
| `vitest` | Latest — unit tests (dev) |
| `eslint`, `eslint-config-next` | Latest **9.x** until config-next supports ESLint 10 |
| Node (VPS + local) | `>=22.12.0` per `engines` — latest **22 LTS** is 22.23.x |
| `@types/node` | Latest **26.x** (Node 22 runtime) |

## Upgrade workflow

```bash
npm outdated
npm update                    # minor/patch within semver ranges
# major bumps: edit package.json ranges, then npm install
npm run lint && npm run check:urdu && npm run build
```

1. Read changelogs for `next`, `sanity`, `next-sanity`, Tailwind, ESLint
2. Never run `npm audit fix --force` if it downgrades Sanity or Next
3. After bump: fix breaking API changes in one focused PR
4. Ship only after `preflight` (+ `build`)

## Pinning exceptions (document here if added)

- **ESLint 9.39.4** — ESLint 10 crashes `eslint-config-next@16` (`eslint-plugin-react` `getFilename()` removed; re-verified 2026-06-20)
- **`postcss@^8.5.15` override** — pins Next nested PostCSS; see `package.json` `overrides`
- No other pins unless a upstream blocker is documented in this file

## Agent behavior

- When touching `package.json`, check `npm outdated` and propose latest compatible versions
- Do not leave stale majors when a safe upgrade path exists
- Update `01-project.mdc` version line only when stack versions change materially
